      UPDATEs _fathomdb_embedder_profiles.mean_vec, and re-quantizes every prior
      row -- all in the same transaction (ports the write_vector_for_test pin
      block into the async path). MeanVecPinned is published only after commit.
    - A new commit_gate Mutex serializes the commit body across the 2 projection
      worker connections, making commit txs totally ordered so the at-pin
      re-quantize is provably complete (no row survives un-centered). Embedding
      stays parallel (outside the gate).
    - ProjectionRuntime::new no longer allocates the accumulator when a mean is
      already pinned, so a later 256-doc run cannot re-pin (compute-once).
    - open_locked adds a recovery pin: MC-required + mean NULL + rows >= threshold
      re-derives and pins from existing un-centered rows (crash-before-pin safety).
    
