commit c719a12be7159730f1b9844d44e724064dc13059
Author: Corey Thompson <coreyt@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri May 29 22:10:21 2026 -0500

    fix(0.7.1): EU-5f Finding C -- truncate embedder input to 512 tokens
    
    CandleBgeEmbedder tokenized with no length cap, so any document over
    BGE-small's 512-slot position-embedding window failed with
    "forward: index-select invalid index 512 with dim size 512" (spec
    violation: embedder-decision.md S2.1 requires truncation True / max 512).
    
    This was the ACTUAL EU-7 seeding stall: long real-corpus docs (cnn_dailymail
    articles, ~corpus index 667+) erred in the projection worker, were retried
    with backoff, and a whole batch of them blew past the per-batch drain timeout
    -> EngineError::Scheduler. A standalone embed probe over the first 800 corpus
    docs reproduced the error at the first >512-token doc with no engine involved.
    
    Fix: configure the tokenizer with with_truncation(max=512) at load, so long
    docs are truncated (re-applying [SEP]) rather than erroring.
    
    - RED: embed_truncates_documents_over_512_tokens (was index-select error)
    - GREEN: all 7 candle_bge tests pass
    - Updates the findings doc (Finding C) and the harness SerializedBge comment.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

